x4freetext: Measurements were performed using the
7Li beam delivered by the SMP Tandem Van de Graaff
accelerator of the INFN-LNS in Catania
The measurements of the elastic scattering angular
distributions of 7Li on 64Zn were performed in two
different experiments-
- in the first experiment the measurements
corresponding to higher energies E(lab)= 18.33 and
20.18 MeV were carried out, while in a second
experiment those corresponding to lower energies
E(lab)= 13.03,13.85,15.08 and 16.60 MeV were performed.
The target was 99.4% enriched 64Zn evaporated onto a
carbon backing, the target thickness was 140 mug/cm**2
on a 60 mug/cm**2 carbon backing in the first
experiment and 110 mug/cm**2 on a 20 mug/cm**2 carbon
backing in the second experiment. A thin 209Bi backing
layer, 2-3 mug/cm**2, was also present in the target
used in the second experiment.
Outgoing charged particles were
detected and identified by an array of five silicon
telescopes,each consisting of a 10 mum thick E detector
followed by a 200 mu-m thick E detector.The angular
separation between two adjacent telescopes was 10 deg.
Telescopes were mounted on rotating support in a
scattering chamber.
.The error bars in the figure represent
statistical uncertainties only.
.The uncertainties in the cross sections due to
the 1n-transfer background depend on the angle and on
the beam energy and could amount up to approx.5% at the
highest measured angles at the highest energies.
S.B.
